- on peut rgler l'intensit des vibrations. De base je les trouve trop fortes et j'ai mis 50%
- on peut mme rgler l'intensit lumineuse du bouton xbox jusqu l'teindre compltement :)

Verr." a beaucoup de potentiel pour les jeux avec beaucoup de commandes (en gros on peut doubler le nombre de commandes par bouton via la pression d'une touche spcifique, exactement comme passer de minuscule majuscule avec un clavier). 1,0 von 5 Sternen 3 Controllers, same DEFECT
Rezension aus dem Vereinigten Knigreich vom 3. Januar 2020
Farbe: Elite BlackPattern Name: ControllerVerifizierter Kauf
So I've ended trying 3 separate Elite 2 Controllers and they all have the same defect which I'm not sure has been noticed by many other people. I thought I might have just been unlucky with the first controller so I got a replacement from Amazon, unfortunately the replacement had the same defect and I returned that one too. I took a punt a few weeks later on a third and same again... same defect. Just for reference, I've owned the first elite since release which I've used on both xbox and pc and have never run into this issue.

The problem... The problem with all of the controllers I tested was related to the LB and RB buttons. Where 50% of the time you pressed (once) either LB or RB the controller would send the input twice. From testing I've found the "2nd" input is sent when you release the button which makes me think its a hardware problem and not software. Now, this might not be so noticeable on some games but on others can make them unplayable. I tested the controllers on both Xbox and PC each with different games and all had the same issue. I'm not sure if Amazon just got a bad batch or if this is more widespread.

This defect is strange because it seems to gradually get worse, when I got my 2nd and 3rd controllers the issue was non-existent on the first day. Yet by day 2 and 3 the issue was starting to get a lot worse. My guess would be this issue is fairly widespread, people just haven't noticed it. Who knows

Steve Griffiths
4,0 von 5 Sternen Almost Perfect
Rezension aus dem Vereinigten Knigreich vom 11. November 2020
Farbe: Shock BluePattern Name: ControllerVerifizierter Kauf
I purchased this controller on release day - the fact that Microsoft is allowing their peripherals to work across multiple platforms is fantastic. It works just as youd expect an Xbox controller to, with some improvements over the previous generation of controllers such as the textured grips and triggers (which I wasnt sold on initially, but they feel great and provide extra grip when your palms get sweaty) as well as the rounded D-Pad which should make rolling your thumb around it slightly easier.

However, its not perfect - for some reason Microsoft have changed the clip at the top of the battery compartment, meaning that any rechargeable battery packs you may have from the previous generation (for example the Venom rechargeable battery packs) simply will not fit in this controller. The controller does come with 2 AA batteries so I can use it until Ive ordered replacement battery packs, however it is hugely disappointing that Microsoft have made this small change to force consumers to fork out extra money on battery packs that fit the new controller.

This is a 5* product, unfortunately it loses a star due to the aforementioned battery compartment change.
